[3] India (West Bengal)
Date: Fri 10 Jul 2009
Source: Times of India [edited]
<http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/Cities/Kolkata-/73-dengue-cases-registered-lens-on-civic-body/articleshow/4760321.cms>


Even before it has got its act together to combat malaria, Kolkata
Municipal Corporation (KMC) now faces the challenge to curb dengue in
the city.

The state health department has already recorded 73 dengue cases this
year [2009]. KMC health department officials conceded that the
situation was quite serious in parts of north Kolkata like
Kankurgachi, Ultadanga and Manicktala that together account for 45
cases. Other affected areas are Camac Street, Bhowanipore, Dhakuria,
Jodhpur Park and Lake Gardens. The health department has asked KMC to
take immediate preventive measures to stop the disease from spreading.

KMC's member, mayor-in-council (health), Subodh De, conceded that the
situation called for immediate civic intervention. "I have heard that
the situation is alarming at some places and have asked KMC health
officials to keep a close tab on the malaria- and dengue-prone areas,"
he said.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett

