[9] Mexico (Jalisco)
Date: Thu 9 Jul 2009
Source: Informador.com.mx [in Spanish, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.informador.com.mx/jalisco/2009/118427/6/enfrenta-tonala-brote-de-dengue.htm>


Tonala is facing a dengue outbreak. It is not known if the virus that
is circulating in the municipality is dengue virus type 1 or 3. The
Tonala municipality has recorded 17 cases of classical dengue [virus
infection], and the other probable cases are under study, which turns
this into the 1st municipality in the Guadalajara Metropolitan Zone
with a dengue outbreak so far this year [2009]. All the cases have
been recorded since the 2nd week of June, in neighboring areas of
Altamira, in Tonala, but it is not known if the virus that is
circulating is type 1 or 3, recently found in the state [Jalisco],
stated the Chief of Epidemiology of the Jalisco Secretariat of Health,
Lucía Salazar Montes.

She indicated that epidemiological surveillance was being done, but it
is of vital importance that patients seek [medical] attention in case
they present with [dengue] symptoms, even more so if they currently
are from the affected neighborhoods.

Salazar Montes reported that in epidemiological [week] 25, which
covers 21 - 27 June [2009], 28 new [dengue] cases were recorded in the
state, only one of which was DHF. During this same week, health region
11 [personnel] identified 4 probable [dengue] cases in the Tonala
neighborhood, which initiated the deliberate search where the rest of
the cases were found.

Up to the present time, the unit has recorded 157 classical dengue
cases and 15 of DHF, for a total of 172 people infected so far this
year [2009].

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The concern is that the greater Guadalajara area, which includes
Mexico's 2nd largest city and satelite cities around it, has a
population of approximately 4 million people, an ample number of hosts
to sustain a significant dengue outbreak if the _Aedes aegypti_
mosquito population is adequate to maintain transmission of the virus.

An interactive map showing the location of Tonala located on the south
east region of the greater Guadalajara area can be accessed at
<http://www.maplandia.com/mexico/jalisco/guadalajara/guadalajara/>

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Mexico can be accessed at
<http://healthmap.org/promed/en?v=24,-102.5,5>
- Mod.TY]
